-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; word-spacing: -0.15ex; text-align: justify; \">\r\n		Hollow ZnSnO<sub style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-size: 0.75em; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; line-height: 0; \">3</sub>&nbsp;nanocubes with peculiar cage- and skeleton-like architectures are successfully synthesized by a simple hydrothermal process at 180&nbsp;&deg;C for 12&nbsp;h. These ZnSnO<sub style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-size: 0.75em; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; line-height: 0; \">3</sub>&nbsp;nanostructures exhibit almost uniform cubic structures with side length of 200&ndash;400&nbsp;nm. The gas sensor based on these ZnSnO<sub style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-size: 0.75em; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; line-height: 0; \">3</sub>&nbsp;nanostructures exhibits high response and quick response-recovery to ethanol and HCHO, which also shows superior sensitive performance compared with the results of sensor based on solid ZnSnO<sub style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-size: 0.75em; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; line-height: 0; \">3</sub>&nbsp;nanocubes.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"sgfNoTitleBar sgfNoGadgetBorder svDoNotLink ui-sortable\" id=\"SD_BA1P\" style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-size: 13px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); font-family: \'Arial Unicode MS\', \'Arial Unicode\', Arial, \'URW Gothic L\', Helvetica, Tahoma, sans-serif; line-height: 20px; \">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h2 id=\"kwd_N1cdb4378N45d23e78\" style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-size: 1.2em; font-weight: 100; margin-top: 20px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 6px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(92, 92, 92); line-height: 1.5em; clear: both; font-family: \'Arial Unicode MS\', \'Arial Unicode\', Arial, \'URW Gothic L\', Helvetica, Tahoma, sans-serif; \">\r\n	Keywords</h2>\r\n<ul class=\"keyword\" style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-size: 13px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-type: none; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); font-family: \'Arial Unicode MS\', \'Arial Unicode\', Arial, \'URW Gothic L\', Helvetica, Tahoma, sans-serif; line-height: 20px; \">\r\n	<li style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; display: inline; \">\r\n		ZnSnO<sub style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-size: 0.75em; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; line-height: 0; \">3</sub>;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; display: inline; \">\r\n		Nanostructure;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; display: inline; \">\r\n		Hydrothermal process;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; display: inline; \">\r\n		Gas sensor</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','Sens. Actuators, B','2009, 143, 449-453','2009-12-04','http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0925400509005814','http://mnsmdlab.googlecode.com/files/Synthesis%20and%20gas-sensing%20properties%20of%20ZnSnO3%20cubic%20nanocages%20and%20nanoskeletons.pdf','../picture/cover/1333461846.gif',NULL),(2009150,'Development of an auto test system for humidity sensors','<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div class=\"abstract svAbstract\" style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-size: 13px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: -2px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); font-family: \'Arial Unicode MS\', \'Arial Unicode\', Arial, \'URW Gothic L\', Helvetica, Tahoma, sans-serif; line-height: 20px; \">\r\n	<p id=\"\" style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; word-spacing: -0.15ex; text-align: justify; \">\r\n		Humidity sensors are fabricated on ceramic substrates with Ag&ndash;Pd interdigitated electrodes by loading ZnO nanorods as a sensing material. X-ray diffraction (XRD) and field-emission scanning electron microscopy (FE-SEM) are applied to characterize these ZnO nanorods. An auto test system is developed by connecting a ZL-5 model LCR analyzer and a PCI&ndash;GPIB interface. Several programs are designed using the LabVIEW environment to measure the humidity sensing properties of our sensors, such as response&ndash;recovery curves, capacitance characteristics, frequency properties, and complex impedance properties. The results make our system a good candidate in sensor investigations.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"sgfNoTitleBar sgfNoGadgetBorder svDoNotLink ui-sortable\" id=\"SD_BA1P\" style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-size: 13px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); font-family: \'Arial Unicode MS\', \'Arial Unicode\', Arial, \'URW Gothic L\', Helvetica, Tahoma, sans-serif; line-height: 20px; \">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h2 id=\"kwd_N22a90218N1d983f28\" style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-size: 1.2em; font-weight: 100; margin-top: 20px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 6px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(92, 92, 92); line-height: 1.5em; clear: both; font-family: \'Arial Unicode MS\', \'Arial Unicode\', Arial, \'URW Gothic L\', Helvetica, Tahoma, sans-serif; \">\r\n	Keywords</h2>\r\n<ul class=\"keyword\" style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-size: 13px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-type: none; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); font-family: \'Arial Unicode MS\', \'Arial Unicode\', Arial, \'URW Gothic L\', Helvetica, Tahoma, sans-serif; line-height: 20px; \">\r\n	<li style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; display: inline; \">\r\n		Auto test system;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; display: inline; \">\r\n		Humidity sensing properties;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; display: inline; \">\r\n		LabVIEW;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; display: inline; \">\r\n		ZL5;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; display: inline; \">\r\n		Sensor</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','Sens. Actuators A','2009, 152, 104-109','2009-05-21','http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0924424709001241','http://mnsmdlab.googlecode.com/files/Development%20of%20an%20auto%20test%20system%20for%20humidity%20sensors.pdf','../picture/cover/1333462204.gif',NULL),(2009160,'Complex Impedance Analysis of the Humidity Sensing Properties of Polypyrrole','<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; Polypyrrole was obtained by chemical synthesis. The extension of polymerization time to 96 h produced a polypyrrole that was suitable for absorbing moisture. The structure and morphology of polypyrrole were characterized by infrared (IR) spectroscopy, X-ray diffraction (XRD), and scanning electron microscopy (SEM). Properties of this humidity sensor were investigated and complex impedance plots were obtained from 20 Hz to 100 kHz. The sensing mechanism was discussed based on test results. Using complex impedance analysis we studied the working principle of the humidity sensor and confirmed the identity of the conductive particles.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	?Key Words?? Polypyrrole Humidity sensor Complex impedance&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	?Fund?? ??????(20060528)????&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	?CateGory Index?? O633.5</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	?DOI?? CNKI:SUN:WLHX.0.2009-02-025</div>\r\n','Acta Phys.Chim.Sin.','2009, 25(2), 327-330','2009-02-01','http://en.cnki.com.cn/Article_en/CJFDTotal-WLHX200902025.htm','http://mnsmdlab.googlecode.com/files/Complex%20Impedance%20Analysis%20of%20the%20Humidity%20Sensing%20Properties%20of%20Polypyrrole.pdf','../picture/cover/1333462857.jpeg',NULL),(2009170,'Synthesis, optical and gas sensitive properties of large-scale aggregative flowerlike ZnO nanostructures via simple route hydrothermal process','<p>\r\n	<span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, Verdana, sans-serif; line-height: 16px; text-align: left; \">Large-scale aggregative flowerlike ZnO nanostructures, consisting of many bunches of nanorods at different orientations with a diameter of about 60 nm and a length of 1 &micro;m, have been synthesized through a simple hydrothermal process at a lower temperature. The x-ray power diffraction pattern indicates that the novel flowerlike ZnO nanostructures are hexagonal, and the selected area electron diffraction reveals that the ZnO nanorods are single crystal in nature and preferentially grow along [0 0 1]. Raman spectrum, room-temperature photoluminescence and UV&ndash;vis absorption spectra are also discussed. Furthermore, the influence of the reaction time on the morphology of the ZnO nanostructures is investigated, and a possible growth model is proposed. Finally, the gas sensor based on the ZnO nanostructures exhibits high sensitivity for ethanol as well as quick response and recovery time due to the high surface-to-volume ratio.</span></p>\r\n','J. Phys. D: Appl. Phys.','2009, 42, 045103','2009-01-15','http://iopscience.iop.org/0022-3727/42/4/045103','http://mnsmdlab.googlecode.com/files/Synthesis%2C%20optical%20and%20gas%20sensitive%20properties%20of%20large-scale%20aggregative%20flowerlike%20ZnO%20nanostructures%20via%20simple%20route%20hydrothermal%20process.pdf','../picture/cover/1333463255.gif',NULL),(2009180,'Synthesis and Ethanol Sensing Properties of Self-Assembled Monocrystalline ZnO Nanorod Bundles by Poly(ethylene glycol)-Assisted Hydrothermal Process','<p>\r\n	<span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; text-align: left; background-color: rgb(244, 249, 253); \">The flowerlike ZnO nanorod bundles, consisting of closely packed nanorods with diameter of&nbsp;</span><img align=\"bottom\" alt=\"\" class=\"entityA\" src=\"http://pubs.acs.org/appl/literatum/publisher/achs/journals/entities/223C.gif\" style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; max-width: 570px; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; text-align: left; background-color: rgb(244, 249, 253); \" /><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; text-align: left; background-color: rgb(244, 249, 253); \">90 nm, have been successfully synthesized by a poly(ethylene glycol) (PEG)-assisted hydrothermal route at low temperature (80 &deg;C). The results characterized from FESEM, TEM, and SAED demonstrate that the nanorod structures are single crystals and formed from self-assembled nanoparticles. Further investigation of the formation mechanism reveals that the PEG-assisted hydrothermal process is vital to the formation of the complex nanostructures. The sensors based on the ZnO nanostructures exhibit excellent ethanol-sensing properties at reduced working temperature (250 &deg;C), which could still respond to 1 ppm ethanol. The sensitivity of the sensor to 100 ppm ethanol is about 154.3 with the response time of 12 s. The enhancement in sensing properties of the present ZnO sensor may be attributed to the peculiar ZnO nanostructures.</span></p>\r\n','J. Phys. Chem. C','2009, 113, 3442-3448','2009-02-09','http://pubs.acs.org/doi/abs/10.1021/jp8082166','http://mnsmdlab.googlecode.com/files/Synthesis%20and%20Ethanol%20Sensing%20Properties%20of%20Self-Assembled%20Monocrystalline%20ZnO%20Nanorod%20Bundles%20by%20Poly%28ethylene%20glycol%29-Assisted%20Hydrothermal%20Process.pdf','../picture/cover/1333463665.jpeg',NULL),(2009190,'Fabrication and Optical Properties of Large-Scale Nutlike ZnO Microcrystals via a Low-Temperature Hydrothermal Route','<p>\r\n	<span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; text-align: left; background-color: rgb(244, 249, 253); \">Large-scale uniform nutlike ZnO microcrystals are successfully synthesized via a facile hydrothermal process. Field emission scanning electron microscopy and transmission electron microscopy results reveal that the as-prepared ZnO products have average lengths of 2.2 &mu;m and diameters of 1.8 &mu;m, possessing a wurtzite structure. The evolution process of the nutlike ZnO microcrystals has been viewed by FESEM characterization, and the results reveal that the reaction time plays a crucial role in determining the final size and shape of the samples. It is also found that the existence of triethanolamine (TEA) is vital to the formation of the complex microcrystals formed from self-assembled nanoparticles, and a possible formation mechanism is proposed. Optical properties of the ZnO sample are also investigated by PL spectroscopy. It is found that the intensity of the visible emission shows an obvious decrease after the nutlike ZnO is annealed in air for 90 min. Moreover, the UV emission is further identified to originate from the recombination of the radiative free exciton and the donor bound excition by the temperature-dependent PL spectra.</span></p>\r\n','J. Phys. Chem. C','2009, 113, 8016-8022','2009-04-15','http://pubs.acs.org/doi/abs/10.1021/jp808939n','http://mnsmdlab.googlecode.com/files/Fabrication%20and%20Optical%20Properties%20of%20Large-Scale%20Nutlike%20ZnO%20Microcrystals%20via%20a%20Low-Temperature%20Hydrothermal%20Route.pdf','../picture/cover/1333464509.jpeg',NULL),(2009200,'One-Pot Synthesis and Gas-Sensing Properties of Hierarchical ZnSnO3 Nanocages','<p>\r\n	<span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; text-align: left; background-color: rgb(244, 249, 253); \">We have successfully fabricated hierarchical ZnSnO</span><sub style=\"vertical-align: -0.4em; font-size: 0.8em; line-height: 0.8em; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: left; background-color: rgb(244, 249, 253); \">3</sub><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; text-align: left; background-color: rgb(244, 249, 253); \">&nbsp;nanocages via a facile one-pot solution synthesis method. Field emission scanning electron microscopic and transmission electron microscopic results reveal that the cubic ZnSnO</span><sub style=\"vertical-align: -0.4em; font-size: 0.8em; line-height: 0.8em; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: left; background-color: rgb(244, 249, 253); \">3</sub><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; text-align: left; background-color: rgb(244, 249, 253); \">&nbsp;samples with hollow interior and porous shells are cage-like structure with the side length of 200&minus;400 nm, where the subunits are irregular-shaped nanoparticles. The time-dependent morphology of the ZnSnO</span><sub style=\"vertical-align: -0.4em; font-size: 0.8em; line-height: 0.8em; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: left; background-color: rgb(244, 249, 253); \">3</sub><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; text-align: left; background-color: rgb(244, 249, 253); \">&nbsp;samples has been investigated, and a possible formation mechanism of these hierarchical structures is proposed. Moreover, gas sensor based on hierarchical ZnSnO</span><sub style=\"vertical-align: -0.4em; font-size: 0.8em; line-height: 0.8em; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: left; background-color: rgb(244, 249, 253); \">3</sub><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; text-align: left; background-color: rgb(244, 249, 253); \">&nbsp;nanocages exhibits better sensing properties compared with the solid ZnSnO</span><sub style=\"vertical-align: -0.4em; font-size: 0.8em; line-height: 0.8em; font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: left; background-color: rgb(244, 249, 253); \">3</sub><span style=\"font-family: \'Trebuchet MS\', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px; text-align: left; background-color: rgb(244, 249, 253); \">&nbsp;nanocubes. The facile preparation method may provide an easy path to the extendable synthesis of other functional nanomaterials with hollow structure and further exploitation of the potential applications.</span></p>\r\n','J. Phys. Chem. C','2009, 113, 19000-19004','2009-10-12','http://pubs.acs.org/doi/abs/10.1021/jp905230h','http://mnsmdlab.googlecode.com/files/One-Pot%20Synthesis%20and%20Gas-Sensing%20Properties%20of%20Hierarchical%20ZnSnO3%20Nanocages.pdf','../picture/cover/1333465055.jpeg',NULL),(2010010,'The humidity-sensitive property of MgO-SBA-15 composites in one-pot synthesis','<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div class=\"abstract svAbstract\" style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-size: 13px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: -2px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); font-family: \'Arial Unicode MS\', \'Arial Unicode\', Arial, \'URW Gothic L\', Helvetica, Tahoma, sans-serif; line-height: 20px; \">\r\n	<p id=\"\" style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; word-spacing: -0.15ex; text-align: justify; \">\r\n		MgO-SBA-15 has been successfully developed as a kind of humidity-sensitive material. The structure of MgO-SBA-15 materials was characterized by XRD, IR spectroscopy, N<sub style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-size: 0.75em; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; line-height: 0; \">2</sub>&nbsp;adsorption&ndash;desorption, TEM and XPS. The study proved that the MgO did not destroy the mesoporous structure of SBA-15 via the characteristic results of XRD and N<sub style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-size: 0.75em; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; line-height: 0; \">2</sub>&nbsp;adsorption&ndash;desorption. Researchers built the thick film humidity sensors on the Al<sub style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-size: 0.75em; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; line-height: 0; \">2</sub>O<sub style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-size: 0.75em; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; line-height: 0; \">3</sub>&nbsp;ceramic substrate with two Ag&ndash;Pd interdigital electrodes with five fingers. The sensor shows excellent humidity sensitivity from 11% to 95%RH, and it has very good response and recovery property. The response time is about 10&nbsp;s and the recovery time is about 20&nbsp;s. We found that the mesoporous structure of the sensing materials contributed to the humidity sensitivity. We discussed a possible mechanism based on the humidity sensor produced by MgO-SBA-15.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"sgfNoTitleBar sgfNoGadgetBorder svDoNotLink ui-sortable\" id=\"SD_BA1P\" style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-size: 13px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); font-family: \'Arial Unicode MS\', \'Arial Unicode\', Arial, \'URW Gothic L\', Helvetica, Tahoma, sans-serif; line-height: 20px; \">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h2 id=\"kwd_N63800d18N1e57931c\" style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-size: 1.2em; font-weight: 100; margin-top: 20px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 6px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(92, 92, 92); line-height: 1.5em; clear: both; font-family: \'Arial Unicode MS\', \'Arial Unicode\', Arial, \'URW Gothic L\', Helvetica, Tahoma, sans-serif; \">\r\n	Keywords</h2>\r\n<ul class=\"keyword\" style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-size: 13px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-type: none; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); font-family: \'Arial Unicode MS\', \'Arial Unicode\', Arial, \'URW Gothic L\', Helvetica, Tahoma, sans-serif; line-height: 20px; \">\r\n	<li style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; display: inline; \">\r\n		MgO-SBA-15;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; display: inline; \">\r\n		Humidity sensor;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; display: inline; \">\r\n		Complex impedance;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; display: inline; \">\r\n		Sensing mechanism</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','Sens. Actuators, B','2010, 145, 386-393','2010-03-04','http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0925400509009617','http://mnsmdlab.googlecode.com/files/The%20humidity-sensitive%20property%20of%20MgO-SBA-15%20composites%20in%20one-pot%20synthesis.pdf','../picture/cover/1333465613.gif',NULL),(2010020,'Humidity sensing properties of BaTiO3 nanofiber prepared via electrospinning','<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div class=\"abstract svAbstract\" style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-size: 13px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: -2px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); font-family: \'Arial Unicode MS\', \'Arial Unicode\', Arial, \'URW Gothic L\', Helvetica, Tahoma, sans-serif; line-height: 20px; \">\r\n	<p id=\"\" style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 9px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; word-spacing: -0.15ex; text-align: justify; \">\r\n		Barium titanate (BaTiO<sub style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-size: 0.75em; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; line-height: 0; \">3</sub>) nanofiber was synthesized by electrospinning and by using the calcinations technique. Its morphologies were characterized by scanning electron microscopy, which showed that its average diameter was 80&ndash;200&nbsp;nm, and its length was over 0.1&nbsp;mm. An impedance-type humidity sensor was then fabricated based on this BaTiO<sub style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-size: 0.75em; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; line-height: 0; \">3</sub>&nbsp;nanofiber. It was unexpected to find that such sensor exhibited fast response and recovery, which were 5 and 4&nbsp;s between 11% and 95% relative humidity, respectively. The long stability and humidity hysteresis properties of this sensor were also tested, and they were found to be optimum. These excellent sensing characteristics prove that BaTiO<sub style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-size: 0.75em; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; line-height: 0; \">3</sub>&nbsp;nanofiber is applicable for high-performance humidity sensors.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"sgfNoTitleBar sgfNoGadgetBorder svDoNotLink ui-sortable\" id=\"SD_BA1P\" style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-size: 13px; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); font-family: \'Arial Unicode MS\', \'Arial Unicode\', Arial, \'URW Gothic L\', Helvetica, Tahoma, sans-serif; line-height: 20px; \">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h2 id=\"kwd_N42e10598N23a41b9c\" style=\"border-top-width: 0px; border-right-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; border-left-width: 0px; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; font-size: 1.2em; font-wei